HEADWORD: Iridoline
<hw>I*rid"o*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Irid</ets>escent + L. <ets>ol</ets>eum oil.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A nitrogenous base <chform>C10H9N</chform>,
extracted from coal-tar naphtha, as an oily liquid. It is a member of
the quinoline series, and is probably identical with
<altname>lepidine</altname>.</def></p>

